er saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705190,"age":20,"year":"1290","julianDay":2192224,"title":"Jews Expelled From England","description":"After years of anti-Semitic behavior, King Edward I expelled Jews from England in 1290.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705191,"age":45,"year":"1315","toYear":"1317","julianDay":2201354,"title":"Famine Strikes Europe","description":"A famine caused by cold winters and wet summers across Europe caused millions to die due to starvation. Desperation from hunger caused high levels of crime, stampedes in bread lines in London, infanticide, and even cannibalism throughout Europe.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705192,"age":58,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705193,"age":67,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705195,"age":112,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and profe